message.entry: Signal constellation must be a vector of at least two elements, representing the set of constellation points that the modulator in the current model can generate.
Channel coefficients must be a column vector whose length is a multiple of the Samples per symbol parameter.
Traceback depth must be a positive integer.
Expected preamble must be a vector of integers between 0 and the order of the constellation minus 1.
Expected postamble must be a vector of integers between 0 and the order of the constellation minus 1.
Samples per symbol must be a positive integer.
MLSE Equalizer parameter settings describe a trellis with more than 2^20 states leading to memory allocation failure
